2011-04-26

    - created new widget-interface (version 0.1.0)
        this widget is now easily embeddable into other
        sites, since it is self-contained - the basic version looks like this:
        
        <script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8" 
        src="http://wwwdup.uni-leipzig.de/jobportal/js/ccul-jobportal-widget-0.1.0.js">
        </script><script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8">
        ccul_jobportal_load.widget("");</script>
        <div id="ccul_jobportal_widget"></div>
        
        that's all. widget uses any existing jquery library if present
        on the hosts page - otherwise it will lazy load jquery from
        our own server - javascript white magic
        
        widget also supports basic customization (search terms, widget width)

    - created web page for creating widget code:
    
        http://wwwdup.uni-leipzig.de/jobportal/widget
        
    - fixed innerHTML bug to make widget cross-platform
    - site-backup (maintenance)

2011-04-25

    - finished read-only API (version 0.1.0), 
        documentation available under

        http://wwwdup.uni-leipzig.de/jobportal/api

    - added small PDf icon as download shortcut to the main
        overview page
    - fixed email regex bug
    - fixed job offer attachment filename, now conforms to CC file naming
        conventions: YYYY_MM_DD_OfferID_CompanyName_JobTitle_JobLocation.pdf
    - fixed routing, so the attachments are really ending in ".pdf" - 
        was at least an issue with wget and the like, e.g.

        http://wwwdup.uni-leipzig.de/jobportal/job/download/1000.pdf

    - site-backup (maintenance)

